fields.physical_description:
1.  box lid, card covered with paper printed in colours to show the title and an illustration of a house.  There is a `Tested and Guaranteed' label, printed in blue and in 5 languages, glued to the inside of the lid.
The box surface is scratched and has one torn area, but otherwise is in good condition.
2.  box base, card covered with blue paper
3.  box lining, large rectangle of plain card
4.  box lining, small rectangle of plain card
5.  box lining tray, cream card, to hold roof panels
6.  box lining tray, cream card, to hold windows and doors
7.  tray cover, clear plastic, for (6), split at corner
8.  box, yellow card with red lettering, for holding metal rods and plates - 
     In the box there are the following rods:-
     9 No.½ - 1.5cm;  17 No.1 - 2.7cm; 1 No.2 - 4.3cm; 28 No. 3 - 6.7cm;
     4 No.4 - 8.6cm
9-13.  corner tie bars, square metal plates each with 9 holes, 2.8cm sq
14-21.  straight tie bars, metal plates each with 5 holes, 4.5 x 0.6cm
22.  booklet, 24 pages printed in red, yellow, green and black on white to show title, illustrations, instructions and parts for the kit.
*Title - BAYKO Registered Trade Mark INSTRUCTIONS FOR OUTFITS Nos. 11,12,13 & 14.  MADE IN ENGLAND BY MECCANO LTD.
23.  Base, B12, moulded grey plastic with the surface covered with lines of holes and pairs of larger holes around the outer edges.  Marked under neath - BAYKO MECCANO LTD MADE IN ENGLAND.  13x9.5x0.7cm
24,25.  Roof A, B142, moulded light green plastic, marked to show tiles
       11.5x4.5x0.5cm
26,27.  Roof End A, B150, moulded white/cream plastic; triangular shape with 5 rod holes along bottom edge and two cut out slots at apex.  W.6.7
28-33.  Brick, B18, moulded red plastic (there should be 11) 1.9cm sq.
34-38.  Brick, B20, moulded white plastic (there should be 9) 1.9cm sq.
39,40.  Brick End, B30, moulded red plastic (there should be 4) 1.9cmsq
41-46.  Brick End, B32, moulded white plastic (there should be 8)1.9cm
47-51.  Brick Half, B36, moulded white plastic (there should be 11 but no red ones in the set), 1.9 x 0.9cm
52,53.  Brick Curved, B26, moulded red plastic, L.4.3cm
54.  Brick Curved, B28, moulded white plastic, L. 4.3cm
55.  Canopy, B80, moulded red plastic with 5 rod holes, 4.8x1.9x0.5cm
56.  Chimney, B82, moulded red plastic, Ht. 1.5cm
57,58.  Door, B94, moulded yellow plastic, 4.8x1.9x0.5cm
59-64.  Window, B190, moulded yellow plastic, 2.8x1.9x0.5cm
65.  Window Curved, B192, moulded yellow plastic, Ht. 2.8cm
66,67.  Glazing Material for B190, clear plastic (there should be 6)
68.  Glazing Material, clear plastic which does not fit any window provided except the large window which is not listed as part of this kit.

Full Title on lid:- YOU CAN BUILD A WIDE VARIETY OF FINE MODELS WITH THIS OUTFIT/BAYKO REGISTERED TRADE MARK/BUILDING OUTFIT 11/ NO. 11 OUTFIT CAN BE CONVERTED INTO NO. 12 BY ADDING NO. 11C. MADE AND GUARANTEED BY MECCANO LIMITED/FOR BOYS & GIRLS OF ALL AGES.

fields.history_note:
References: price label on side in pen - 11/3
Bayko kits were patented, 1935, by Charles Bird Plimpton of Plimpton Engineering Co Ltd, Liverpool, a long established toymaking firm. 

The donor was born in 1959 and had this kit as a boy.
fields.production_note: Made by: Meccano Ltd., Binns Road, Liverpool, England
